  "story": [
    "Lording it at the top, <b>Quince</b> is boring everyone into an early grave &mdash; 6 clean sheets, zero entertainment. The kind of football that makes people emigrate. Smugly in tow, <b>Sid</b> has turned the goalless draw into an art form nobody asked for &mdash; 6 of them. A black hole where fun goes to die. Rounding out the insufferable elite, <b>Big Pewerk</b>'s lot defend like the door's been left on the latch, but they'll at least outscore the misery &mdash; 28 goals (GD +1), led by Netherlands (beautiful football, then a fistfight among themselves). Thrilling, doomed.",
    "Wallowing in mid-table sludge, <b>Ike</b> saw something in Uzbekistan (the tournament's great unmarked mystery box) that no scout, coach or sane human ever has &mdash; played, did nothing, and is somehow still the jewel of that abysmal squad. Equally forgettable, <b>Ellie</b>'s defence is a public health hazard &mdash; 28 shipped, Qatar (lavishly funded, modestly threatening) leaking 10 of them. Genuinely embarrassing to be associated with. Barely clinging to relevance, <b>Etan</b> will be replaying Senegal (power, pace and swagger for days)'s 5-0 all tournament because, let's be honest, it's the only good thing their team will ever do. Frame it.",
    "Down in the dregs, <b>Murray</b> had to sit and watch New Zealand (the All Whites: good time, not a long time) get battered 1-5 &mdash; and we'll be bringing it up at every opportunity for the rest of their natural life. And scraping the very bottom of the barrel, <b>Elsa</b> spread their picks out of sheer cowardice &mdash; 4 teams all contributing scraps, not one brave enough to actually be good. Death by committee."
  ],
